Peachy is an interpreted scripting language.

Software design goals:

- Don't use any external dependencies other than std and stl
- Be multi-platform from a single build system
- Support unit testing and mock objects to the hilt
- Have complete and clear documentation
- Have a complete test suit

Language design goals:

- Simple syntax
- Support XML as a language construct (a la Scala)
- Support JSON as a language construct
- Simple syntax
